intro to time series wrangling & viz

Logan Kozal

1/25/2021

Read in the data

toolik <- read_csv(here::here("data","toolikweather.csv")) 
## Parsed with column specification:
## cols(
##   date = col_character(),
##   station = col_character(),
##   mean_airtemp = col_double(),
##   daily_precip = col_double(),
##   mean_windspeed = col_double()
## )

Convert this into a tsibble

toolik_ts <- toolik %>% 
  mutate(date = lubridate::mdy(date)) %>% 
  as_tsibble(key = NULL, index = date)
ggplot(data = toolik_ts, aes( x = date, y = mean_airtemp))+
  geom_line()

Use the index_by() function to aggregate time series information by intervals we specify

toolik_month <- toolik_ts %>% 
  index_by(yr_mo = ~yearmonth(.)) %>% 
  summarize(monthly_mean_temp = mean(mean_airtemp, na.rm = TRUE))

ggplot(data = toolik_month, aes(x = yr_mo, y = monthly_mean_temp))+
  geom_line() +
  facet_wrap(~month(yr_mo, label = TRUE))

aggregate by week

toolik_weekly <- toolik_ts %>% 
  index_by(weekly = ~yearweek(.)) %>% 
  summarize(weekly_airtemp = mean(mean_airtemp, na.rm = TRUE, min_airtemp = min(mean_airtemp)))

Filtering time series

Use filter_index() to specify ranges of time series to keep or exclude

toolik_ts %>% 
  filter_index("2006-06" ~ "2001-10")

Seasonplots

toolik_ts %>% 
  filter(year(date) > 2014) %>% 
  gg_season(y=mean_airtemp)

toolik_month %>% 
  gg_season(y = monthly_mean_temp)+
  theme_light()

Find moving average

Using the slider package in R

set.seed(2021)
test <- rnorm(n=100, mean=40, sd=10)


slide(test, ~.x, .before = 2, .after=2)

#original output is list, have to convert to numeric
roll_toolik_15 <- toolik_ts %>% 
  mutate(ma_15d = as.numeric(slide(toolik_ts$mean_airtemp, 
                                   mean,
                                   .before = 7,
                                   .after = 7)))

ggplot()+
  geom_line(data = toolik_ts, aes(x = date, y = mean_airtemp),
                                  size=0.2,
                                  color="gray")+
  geom_line(data = roll_toolik_15, aes(x = date, y= ma_15d))

  theme_minimal()

Create the ACF

toolik_ts %>% 
  ACF(mean_airtemp) %>% 
  autoplot()

toolik_month %>% 
  ACF(monthly_mean_temp) %>% 
  autoplot()

## STL Decomposition slightly different smoothing compared to classical

toolik_dec <- toolik_month %>% model(STL(monthly_mean_temp ~ season(window = Inf)))

components(toolik_dec) %>% autoplot()
